            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy outlines how the **BCA Examiner Allotment System** collects, uses, and protects your data.</p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details such as **name, email, and phone number** for user registration.</li>
                <li>College information including **address, pincode, and contact persons**.</li>
                <li>System usage data, including logins and examiner allotments.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To manage **examiner allotments efficiently**.</li>
                <li>To provide **secure access** to authorized users.</li>
                <li>To improve the system based on user interactions.</li>
                <li>To comply with legal and university policies.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement strict **security measures** to prevent unauthorized access, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encryption of sensitive data.</li>
                <li>Role-based access control.</li>
                <li>Regular security updates.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell or rent your data. However, we may share information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>With university administrators for **academic and examination purposes**.</li>
                <li>If required by law enforcement or government authorities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Request **access** to your personal data.</li>
                <li>Request **corrections** to incorrect data.</li>
                <li>Request **deletion** of your data (subject to policies).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>7. Changes to this Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Significant changes will be notified via the system.</p>

            <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any concerns regarding this policy, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>

        
